<div id="simulating-populations-and-surveys" class="section level2">
<h2>2. Simulating Populations and Surveys</h2>
<p>To test the method or plan study designs, the DOAS package includes
functions to simulate realistic cluster-sampled populations.</p>
<div id="simulating-a-population-simulate_pop" class="section level3">
<h3>Simulating a Population (<code>simulate_pop</code>)</h3>
<p><code>simulate_pop()</code> distributes a simulated population into
logical sectors and groups.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb4"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb4-1"><a href="#cb4-1" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">set.seed</span>(<span class="dv">42</span>)</span>
<span id="cb4-2"><a href="#cb4-2" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Simulate ~1000 individuals, mean group size 10, spread across 15 sectors</span></span>
<span id="cb4-3"><a href="#cb4-3" tabindex="-1"></a>simulated_population <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">simulate_pop</span>(</span>
<span id="cb4-4"><a href="#cb4-4" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">pop_size =</span> <span class="dv">1000</span>,</span>
<span id="cb4-5"><a href="#cb4-5" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">mean_group =</span> <span class="dv">10</span>,</span>
<span id="cb4-6"><a href="#cb4-6" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">tot_areas =</span> <span class="dv">15</span></span>
<span id="cb4-7"><a href="#cb4-7" tabindex="-1"></a>)</span>
<span id="cb4-8"><a href="#cb4-8" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb4-9"><a href="#cb4-9" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Total simulated individuals</span></span>
<span id="cb4-10"><a href="#cb4-10" tabindex="-1"></a>simulated_population<span class="sc">$</span>tot_pop</span>
<span id="cb4-11"><a href="#cb4-11" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt; [1] 1043</span></span></code></pre></div>
</div>
<div id="simulating-a-doas-survey-simulate_survey" class="section level3">
<h3>Simulating a DOAS Survey (<code>simulate_survey</code>)</h3>
<p><code>simulate_survey()</code> takes the “true” population and
applies detection probabilities to mimic field data collection.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb5"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb5-1"><a href="#cb5-1" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Simulate field observers surveying the population</span></span>
<span id="cb5-2"><a href="#cb5-2" tabindex="-1"></a>survey_data <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">simulate_survey</span>(</span>
<span id="cb5-3"><a href="#cb5-3" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">sim_pop =</span> simulated_population<span class="sc">$</span>sim_pop,</span>
<span id="cb5-4"><a href="#cb5-4" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">det_p1 =</span> <span class="fl">0.6</span>, <span class="co"># Observer 1 spots ~60% of groups</span></span>
<span id="cb5-5"><a href="#cb5-5" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">intra_group_det =</span> <span class="fl">0.9</span>, <span class="co"># Observers typically undercount groups (count 90% of individuals)</span></span>
<span id="cb5-6"><a href="#cb5-6" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">det_group =</span> <span class="fl">0.5</span>, <span class="co"># Group size scaling factor</span></span>
<span id="cb5-7"><a href="#cb5-7" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">obs_effect =</span> <span class="fl">0.75</span>, <span class="co"># Observer 2 is 75% as effective as Observer 1</span></span>
<span id="cb5-8"><a href="#cb5-8" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">detvar =</span> <span class="fl">0.2</span>, <span class="co"># Variance in detection across different sectors</span></span>
<span id="cb5-9"><a href="#cb5-9" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">surv_areas =</span> <span class="dv">5</span> <span class="co"># Out of 15 areas, 5 will get Double Observers</span></span>
<span id="cb5-10"><a href="#cb5-10" tabindex="-1"></a>)</span>
<span id="cb5-11"><a href="#cb5-11" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb5-12"><a href="#cb5-12" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">head</span>(survey_data)</span>
<span id="cb5-13"><a href="#cb5-13" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt;   sector_id total_count groups_both groups_obs1 groups_obs2 detected_groups</span></span>
<span id="cb5-14"><a href="#cb5-14" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt; 1         1          45           1           6           1               8</span></span>
<span id="cb5-15"><a href="#cb5-15" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt; 2         2          52           1           1           1               3</span></span>
<span id="cb5-16"><a href="#cb5-16" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt; 3         3          25          NA          NA          NA               4</span></span>
<span id="cb5-17"><a href="#cb5-17" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt; 4         4          30          NA          NA          NA               3</span></span>
<span id="cb5-18"><a href="#cb5-18" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt; 5         5           8           0           1           0               1</span></span>
<span id="cb5-19"><a href="#cb5-19" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#&gt; 6         6          11          NA          NA          NA               1</span></span></code></pre></div>
<p>This output is automatically formatted and ready to be plugged into
<code>doas()</code>!</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb6"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb6-1"><a href="#cb6-1" tabindex="-1"></a>sim_results <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">doas</span>(survey_data, <span class="at">method =</span> <span class="st">&quot;hybrid&quot;</span>, <span class="at">obs_type =</span> <span class="st">&quot;bayesian&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb6-2"><a href="#cb6-2" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">summary</span>(sim_results)</span>
