<div id="power-analysis-doas_power" class="section level2">
<h2>3. Power Analysis (<code>doas_power</code>)</h2>
<p>If you are planning a field season, you can use
<code>doas_power()</code> to understand how many DO surveys you need to
achieve reliable confidence intervals and minimize bias.</p>
<p><code>doas_power()</code> runs multiple simulated surveys under the
hood and reports metrics like Relative Bias, Root Mean Squared Error
(RMSE), and 95% CI Coverage.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb7"><pre class="sourceCode r"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb7-1"><a href="#cb7-1" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Run a quick power analysis testing 2 vs 5 DO sectors</span></span>
<span id="cb7-2"><a href="#cb7-2" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Note: For real power analysis, increase n_sims (e.g., 500)</span></span>
<span id="cb7-3"><a href="#cb7-3" tabindex="-1"></a>power_results <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">doas_power</span>(</span>
<span id="cb7-4"><a href="#cb7-4" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">n_sims =</span> <span class="dv">10</span>,</span>
<span id="cb7-5"><a href="#cb7-5" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">surv_areas =</span> <span class="fu">c</span>(<span class="dv">2</span>, <span class="dv">5</span>), <span class="co"># Test scenarios: 2 DO sectors vs 5 DO sectors</span></span>
<span id="cb7-6"><a href="#cb7-6" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">pop_size =</span> <span class="dv">1000</span>,</span>
<span id="cb7-7"><a href="#cb7-7" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">mean_group =</span> <span class="dv">10</span>,</span>
<span id="cb7-8"><a href="#cb7-8" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">tot_areas =</span> <span class="dv">15</span>,</span>
<span id="cb7-9"><a href="#cb7-9" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">method =</span> <span class="st">&quot;hybrid&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb7-10"><a href="#cb7-10" tabindex="-1"></a>)</span>
<span id="cb7-11"><a href="#cb7-11" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb7-12"><a href="#cb7-12" tabindex="-1"></a>knitr<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">kable</span>(power_results, <span class="at">digits =</span> <span class="dv">3</span>)</span></code></pre></div>
